netSnmpAgentMIB.name: netSnmpAgentMIB

revisions.description: Made sure that this MIB can be compiled by MIB compilers that do not recognize a double dash as end-of-comments.

netSnmpAgentMIB.contactinfo: postal: Wes Hardaker P.O. Box 382 Davis CA 95617 email: net-snmp-coders@lists.sourceforge.net
netSnmpAgentMIB.description: Defines control and monitoring structures for the Net-SNMP agent.

NetsnmpCacheStatus.name: NetsnmpCacheStatus
NetsnmpCacheStatus.description: an indication of the status of data caching entries

nsCacheDefaultTimeout.name: nsCacheDefaultTimeout
nsCacheDefaultTimeout.description: Default cache timeout value (unless overridden for a particular cache entry).

nsCacheEnabled.name: nsCacheEnabled
nsCacheEnabled.description: Whether data caching is active overall.

nsCacheTable.name: nsCacheTable
nsCacheTable.description: A table of individual MIB module data caches.

nsCacheEntry.name: nsCacheEntry
nsCacheEntry.description: A conceptual row within the cache table.

nsCachedOID.name: nsCachedOID
nsCachedOID.description: The root OID of the data being cached.

nsCacheTimeout.name: nsCacheTimeout
nsCacheTimeout.description: The length of time (?in seconds) for which the data in this particular cache entry will remain valid.

nsCacheStatus.name: nsCacheStatus
nsCacheStatus.description: The current status of this particular cache entry. Acceptable values for Set requests are 'enabled(1)', 'disabled(2)' or 'empty(3)' (to clear all cached data). Requests to read the value of such an object will return 'disabled(2)' through to 'expired(5)'.

nsDebugEnabled.name: nsDebugEnabled
nsDebugEnabled.description: Whether the agent is configured to generate debugging output

nsDebugOutputAll.name: nsDebugOutputAll
nsDebugOutputAll.description: Whether the agent is configured to display all debugging output rather than filtering on individual debug tokens. Nothing will be generated unless nsDebugEnabled is also true(1)

nsDebugDumpPdu.name: nsDebugDumpPdu
nsDebugDumpPdu.description: Whether the agent is configured to display raw packet dumps. This is unrelated to the nsDebugEnabled setting.

nsDebugTokenTable.name: nsDebugTokenTable
nsDebugTokenTable.description: A table of individual debug tokens, used to control the selection of what debugging output should be produced. This table is only effective if nsDebugOutputAll is false(2), and nothing will be generated unless nsDebugEnabled is also true(1)

nsDebugTokenEntry.name: nsDebugTokenEntry
nsDebugTokenEntry.description: A conceptual row within the debug token table.

nsDebugTokenPrefix.name: nsDebugTokenPrefix
nsDebugTokenPrefix.description: A token prefix for which to generate the corresponding debugging output. Note that debug output will be generated for all registered debug statements sharing this prefix (rather than an exact match). Nothing will be generated unless both nsDebuggingEnabled is set true(1) and the corresponding nsDebugTokenStatus value is active(1).

nsDebugTokenStatus.name: nsDebugTokenStatus
nsDebugTokenStatus.description: Whether to generate debug output for the corresponding debug token prefix. Nothing will be generated unless both nsDebuggingEnabled is true(1) and this instance is active(1). Note that is valid for an instance to be left with the value notInService(2) indefinitely - i.e. the meaning of 'abnormally long' (see RFC 2579, RowStatus) for this table is infinite.

nsLoggingTable.name: nsLoggingTable
nsLoggingTable.description: A table of individual logging output destinations, used to control where various levels of output from the agent should be directed.

nsLoggingEntry.name: nsLoggingEntry
nsLoggingEntry.description: A conceptual row within the logging table.

nsLogLevel.name: nsLogLevel
nsLogLevel.description: The (minimum) priority level for which this logging entry should be applied.

nsLogToken.name: nsLogToken
nsLogToken.description: A token for which to generate logging entries. Depending on the style of logging, this may either be simply an arbitrary token, or may have some particular meaning (such as the filename to log to).

nsLogType.name: nsLogType
nsLogType.description: The type of logging for this entry.

nsLogMaxLevel.name: nsLogMaxLevel
nsLogMaxLevel.description: The maximum priority level for which this logging entry should be applied.

nsLogStatus.name: nsLogStatus
nsLogStatus.description: Whether to generate logging output for this entry. Note that is valid for an instance to be left with the value notInService(2) indefinitely - i.e. the meaning of 'abnormally long' (see RFC 2579, RowStatus) for this table is infinite.

nsTransactionTable.name: nsTransactionTable
nsTransactionTable.description: Lists currently outstanding transactions in the net-snmp agent. This includes requests to AgentX subagents, or proxied SNMP agents.

nsTransactionEntry.name: nsTransactionEntry
nsTransactionEntry.description: A row describing a given transaction.

nsTransactionID.name: nsTransactionID
nsTransactionID.description: The internal identifier for a given transaction.

nsTransactionMode.name: nsTransactionMode
nsTransactionMode.description: The mode number for the current operation being performed.

nsModuleTable.name: nsModuleTable
nsModuleTable.description: A table displaying all the oid's registered by mib modules in the agent. Since the agent is modular in nature, this lists each module's OID it is responsible for and the name of the module

nsModuleEntry.name: nsModuleEntry
nsModuleEntry.description: An entry containing a registered mib oid.

nsmContextName.name: nsmContextName
nsmContextName.description: The context name the module is registered under.

nsmRegistrationPoint.name: nsmRegistrationPoint
nsmRegistrationPoint.description: The registry OID of a mib module.

nsmRegistrationPriority.name: nsmRegistrationPriority
nsmRegistrationPriority.description: The priority of the registered mib module.

nsModuleName.name: nsModuleName
nsModuleName.description: The module name that registered this OID.

nsModuleModes.name: nsModuleModes
nsModuleModes.description: The modes that the particular lower level handler can cope with directly.

nsModuleTimeout.name: nsModuleTimeout
nsModuleTimeout.description: The registered timeout. This is only meaningful for handlers that expect to return results at a later date (subagents, etc)

nsNotifyStart.name: nsNotifyStart
nsNotifyStart.description: An indication that the agent has started running.

nsNotifyShutdown.name: nsNotifyShutdown
nsNotifyShutdown.description: An indication that the agent is in the process of being shut down.

nsNotifyRestart.name: nsNotifyRestart
nsNotifyRestart.description: An indication that the agent has been restarted. This does not imply anything about whether the configuration has changed or not (unlike the standard coldStart or warmStart traps)

nsModuleGroup.name: nsModuleGroup
nsModuleGroup.description: The objects relating to the list of MIB modules registered with the Net-SNMP agent.

nsCacheGroup.name: nsCacheGroup
nsCacheGroup.description: The objects relating to data caching in the Net-SNMP agent.

nsDebugGroup.name: nsDebugGroup
nsDebugGroup.description: The objects relating to debug configuration in the Net-SNMP agent.

nsLoggingGroup.name: nsLoggingGroup
nsLoggingGroup.description: The objects relating to logging configuration in the Net-SNMP agent.

nsTransactionGroup.name: nsTransactionGroup
nsTransactionGroup.description: The objects relating to transaction monitoring in the Net-SNMP agent.

nsAgentNotifyGroup.name: nsAgentNotifyGroup
nsAgentNotifyGroup.description: The notifications relating to the basic operation of the Net-SNMP agent.
